  "text": "There have been many attempts to model the wear rate of various workpiece materials over a wide range of operating conditions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Among them, Hsu and Shen [CITATION_5] expressed the wear rate of ceramics (I V = dV/dS, where V is the wear volume (m 3 ), and S is the sliding distance (m)) as a function of the cutting force and temperature as",
